If the ground colour is not taken into account, the shells lacking not only the top two bands, but also all five bands were absent much more often in the first group of samples (
table 3
). Also, there were more frequent cases when several hereditary traits, associated with the complete or partial absence of dark spiral bands on the shell, were absent in one sample: unbanded and three-banded, mid-banded and three-banded.

